                            <comment id="13433593" author="jesse_yates" created="Mon, 13 Aug 2012 21:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking this to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5487&quot; title=&quot;Generic framework for Master-coordinated tasks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-5487&quot;&gt;HBASE-5487&lt;/a&gt; since it would make sense for dealing with multiple, async, running tasks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13433596" author="jesse_yates" created="Mon, 13 Aug 2012 21:46:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch and design doc, posting to RB momentarily.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13434334" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 14 Aug 2012 18:00:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Really like the fault injection facility.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should not have two error notification frameworks (this and Abortable) coexisting for long.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13434343" author="jesse_yates" created="Tue, 14 Aug 2012 18:07:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Andrew&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;We should not have two error notification frameworks (this and Abortable) coexisting for long.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d argue that we can have both, but we can wrap the abortable code (which is a nice abstraction) into the general framework.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13434347" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 14 Aug 2012 18:13:10 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;we can wrap the abortable code (which is a nice abstraction) into the general framework.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This gets us to the same place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437105" author="jmhsieh" created="Fri, 17 Aug 2012 22:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;review board here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/6589/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/6589/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437321" author="jmhsieh" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2012 13:20:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not convinced that Abortable is at the same level as this framework and that &quot;one shall stand and one shall fall&quot; &amp;#8211; Abortable is essentially for killing a parent process (RS/HM/HBCK/Client) while this is more of just a thread or possibly remote process.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13437414" author="stack" created="Sat, 18 Aug 2012 21:26:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doc is missing an author and date and link to the issue.  I stuck some review up on RB.  Agree this is something else than Abortable (Abortable could add an error to this error bus)&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="13456446" author="jesse_yates" created="Sat, 15 Sep 2012 17:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for commit from Hseih on RB... waiting another day for any other comments, but otherwise will commit to branch (modulo nits).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13457208" author="jesse_yates" created="Mon, 17 Sep 2012 18:29:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing - committed to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jyates/hbase/tree/snapshots&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jyates/hbase/tree/snapshots&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
